    Title: Bhagavad-Gîtâ
    Locus: II 70
Tags:
  - Union-Identity=Holiness-Universal Man=Incorruptibility
---
As the ocean remains calm and unaltered though the waters flow into it,
similarly a self-controlled saint remains unmoved when desires enter into him;
such a saint alone attains peace, but not he who craves the objects of desire.
